Here’s another video showing the process of a classic Ne-Maki Shibori On an Extra Large High Quality Bath Sheet🏖☀️ Who’s ready for summer already cause I know I am! 

for anyone wondering the breakdown of the 4 hours it takes and hour to tie, an hour to dye properly, 48 hours wait before I spend an hour rinsing and unwrapping (which is almost as difficult as tying and dyeing them). on to a wash with special soap to suspend the loose dye and remove it, preventing back staining on the white. Once Its hung dry I than spend however much time is needed steaming, pressing, Sewing, and Tagging it. It’s a very long and exhausting process to produce for you the Highest quality hand dyed art. Thats why I thank each and every one of our supporters from the bottom of my heart.🤟🏼

Head over to DaneWade.com and see what vibe is right for you. link in bio!
